Question One     (12 Points)      (SO’s: 1, 3, 6) 
a) Based on Vigenère Autokey system, use your last name as a keyword, encrypt the following 
sentence: “attack will occur tomorrow”. 
b) Based on AES-128 symmetric encryption, the 128-bit block of data to be encrypted is the 
first sixteen letters of your full name coded in ASCII-hexadecimal (use your full name 
without spaces and if your full name less than sixteen letters, repeat it until reach sixteen). 
Apply a Substitution-Bytes operation using the standard Substitution Box and then follow it 
by a Shift-Rows operation. Show the detailed steps and the result in state arrays (4x4).   
 
Question Two    (8 Points)      (SO’s: 1, 3, 6) 
You are planning to have a secure communication with one of your friends using DES algorithm 
to encrypt the messages. You decide to use the first eight letters of your full name (without 
spaces) coded by ASCII as the key of the algorithm, but you want to exchange this key with 
your friend using RSA algorithm. Your private / public keys pair is PRA= {41, 133} and PUA= 
{29, 133} and the private / public keys pair of your friend is PRB= {23, 187} and PUB= {7, 187}. 
Suppose you know the public keys of each other, and the key exchange mechanism must 
achieve secrecy and authentication. Apply the RSA algorithm showing the detailed steps of 
the encryption algorithms to get the encrypted key that you will send to your friend. 
 
Question Three     (6 Points)      (SO’s: 1, 3, 6) 
Sketch the block diagram(s) that fulfil each of the following security requirements: 
a) Based on public-key cryptography, Alice needs to send a message to Bob. It’s required to 
ensure that no one can know the content of the message except Bob and also Bob requires to 
ensure that the message is originated from Alice. 
b) Alice needs to send a confidential and digitally signed message to Bob, the confidentiality 
must be fulfilled using symmetric key algorithm, so they have to exchange the keys first. 
Suppose that they have each other public key certificates and the digital signature must be 
fulfilled by cryptographic hash algorithm. 
c) An application running on a client side needs to connect to its server side securely over a 
connection-oriented protocol. The application requires AES encryption for confidentiality 
and MAC based on SHA512 for message integrity. Suppose that they don’t have each other 
public key certificate. 
 
